title: What's your "AQI" IQ? What to know, what to do, to improve air quality and your health - Purdue University
text:
About this Event
In this webinar, we bring together Indiana-based specialists in the latest research on (mostly) indoor air quality in order to provide important new understandings of how air quality impacts the health of Hoosiers and how you can improve air quality in your home, at work, and in Indiana day cares and schools. The panel will also discuss current programs, policies and regulations regarding indoor air quality and what impacts poor air quality can have on your health.
Topics include: Air quality and why it matters; How we contribute to our own air quality; what we don't see may hurt us; how to make our home, and our air, safer and healthier; air quality on community, state and federal levels
Co-sponsors: Purdue's Institute for a Sustainable Future; Hoosier Environmental Council, IU Environmental Resilience Institute
Speakers:
Brandon Boor (PU)
Nusrat Jung (PU)
Jocelyn Keranyn (HEC)
Heidi Beidinger-Burnett (ND)
Janet McCabe (IU)
